==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water barometer
<hw>Wa"ter ba*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A
barometer in which the changes of atmospheric pressure are indicated by
the motion of a column of water instead of mercury. It requires a column
of water about thirty-three feet in height.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water bath</ent>⟦br⟧
